  "name": "Globe of Negation",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/items/armor/shield-heavy-metal.png",
  "sort": 0,
  "flags": {},
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As a standard action, you can expend 3 points of mental focus to create a stationary globe of negation. This globe is 10 feet in diameter and cancels any spell effect that is cast into or through its area. This functions as&nbsp;globe of invulnerability, but it affects spells of any level. The globe can negate a total number of spell levels equal to your occultist level, after which the globe collapses.</p>\n<p>Spells that exceed the number of remaining levels remove all remaining levels, but are weakened; any creatures targeted by such spells receive a +4 circumstance bonus on any saving throws against the spells’ effects. The globe lasts for a number of rounds equal to your occultist level. It has no effect on spells originating within the globe—only on those that enter its area as or after they are cast.</p>\n<p>You must be at least 11th level to select this focus power.</p>"
    },
